Lawless creatures have no use for the ethical codes society imposes.  Though 
they do not go out of their way to break laws, they will if they feel they 
must, in order to attain their goals.  Lawless ethics can also indicate 
someone who is an individualist and who sees no need for outwardly-
imposed rules of behavior.  In this way, a lawless creature can still be a 
good individual, just as a lawful creature can be evil in nature.
